# Task: Mobile Navbar Vertical Expand (GSAP)

## What to do

Replace the current floating mobile menu with an **in-place vertical expand** of the navbar itself.
When the burger is tapped, the navbar container stretches downward to reveal the links.
No drawer, no overlay, no fixed panel.

**Do not touch desktop navbar layout, styles, or behaviour at all.**

---

## Behaviour spec

- Burger tap → navbar grows downward, links stagger up into view
- Burger/close tap → navbar collapses back to original height
- Links animate: opacity 0→1, y 10→0, staggered 60ms apart
- A subtle 1px divider line draws in (scaleX 0→1) above the links
- Hover on each link: slides right 4px, chevron brightens — driven by GSAP, not CSS
- Body scroll is NOT locked (the navbar is in-flow, not an overlay)
- `md:hidden` on the component — zero effect on desktop

---

## Files

- **`MobileNavExpand.jsx`** — attached, place alongside your Navbar component
- Your existing **Navbar component** — 3 small changes below

