## Step 3 — Wire into your Navbar component

### 3a — Import
```jsx
import { MobileNavExpand } from "./MobileNavExpand";
```

### 3b — Add state (inside Navbar function)
```jsx
const [mobileOpen, setMobileOpen] = useState(false);
```

### 3c — Connect your burger button
Find your existing hamburger/menu toggle button and update it:
```jsx
<button
  onClick={() => setMobileOpen(prev => !prev)}
  className="md:hidden"
  aria-label={mobileOpen ? "Close menu" : "Open menu"}
>
  {/* your existing icon — or swap for X when open: */}
  {mobileOpen ? <XIcon /> : <MenuIcon />}
</button>
```

### 3d — Mount the expand component INSIDE your navbar container

This is the key difference from the previous implementation.
Place `<MobileNavExpand>` **inside** your existing `<nav>` or navbar wrapper div,
**after** the top bar row (logo + burger row), so it expands the navbar downward:

```jsx
<nav style={{ /* your existing navbar styles */ }}>

  {/* Your existing top bar: logo left, links center (desktop), burger right */}
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4">
    <Logo />
    <DesktopLinks />   {/* already md:flex hidden on mobile */}
    <button onClick={() => setMobileOpen(p => !p)} className="md:hidden">
      {mobileOpen ? <XIcon /> : <MenuIcon />}
    </button>
  </div>

  {/* ↓ ADD THIS — expands the navbar vertically on mobile */}
  <MobileNavExpand
    isOpen={mobileOpen}
    onClose={() => setMobileOpen(false)}
  />

</nav>
```

### 3e — Remove / comment out your old mobile menu
Find the existing mobile menu JSX (likely a div with `md:hidden` that shows links)
and remove it or comment it out:

```jsx
{/* Removed — replaced by MobileNavExpand */}
{/* <div className="md:hidden absolute top-full ..."> ... </div> */}
```

---

## Critical: navbar container must NOT have overflow:hidden

If your `<nav>` or its wrapper has `overflow: hidden` in its styles or Tailwind classes,
remove it — otherwise the expanding links will be clipped.

If you need to keep a border-radius on the navbar, add `overflow: visible` explicitly
and handle the radius on inner elements instead.

